spirit:enumeration.spirit:text: Use STARTUP Primitive External to IP
Use STARTUP Primitive Internal to IP

spirit:component.spirit:description: SPI Interface for SPI Based Slave

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_SPI_MEMORY
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set for tagetting the SPI flash memory. Please refer PG for more reference. Allowed values are 0= Mixed Flash, 1= Winbond SPI Flash, 2= Micron SPI Flash(Numonyx), 3= Spansion SPI Flash.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_USE_STARTUP
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set when the targeted FPGA have STARTUPE2 primitive for routing the SPI clock. Please refer PG for more reference. Allowed values are 0= STARTUP is not included, 1= STARTUP is included. Example Design is not supported when STARTUPE2 primitive is chosen in the design.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_USE_STARTUP_INT
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter will determine if the STARTUP primitive is instantiated with-in IP or outside

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_SPI_MODE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing the SPI mode of the core. Please refer PG for more reference. Allowed values are 0= Standard SPI mode, 1= Dual SPI mode, 2= Quad SPI mode.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_NUM_TRANSFER_BITS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing the no. of bits in single SPI transaction. Please refer PG for more reference. Allowed values are 8 or 16 or 32. The Standard SPI mode supports all the three values while Dual and Quad SPI mode supports only the 8-bit transfer mode.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_NUM_SS_BITS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set to choose the no. SPI slave memories in design. This parameter decides the length of Slave Select port width of the core.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_SCK_RATIO
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing the division ratio for SPI clock. Please refer PG for more reference. Standard SPI mode has variable values for division ratio for SPI clock, while Dual and Quad mode allows only 2. XIP mode also allows division ratio of 2.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_FIFO_DEPTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing FIFO depth. Please refer PG for more reference. Standard SPI mode provides the choice 0 or 16 or 256 beat FIFO depth, while Dual and Quad mode provides options of 16 or 256 beat FIFO depth.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_XIP_MODE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing the core to operate in eXecute In Place (XIP) mode. Please refer PG for more reference.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_TYPE_OF_AXI4_INTERFACE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing the type of AXI bus interface.Please refer PG for more reference. Allowed values are 0= AXI4 Lite Interface, 1= AXI4 Memory Mapped Interface.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: Master_mode
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing the core in Standard SPI mode. Please refer PG for more reference. Standard SPI mode can operate in Master SPI or Slave SPI mode, while Dual and Quad mode operates only in Master SPI mode.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: FIFO_INCLUDED
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing to include the FIFO in the design or notPlease refer PG for more reference. This parameter can be set only in Standard SPI mode where choice of FIFO inclusion or exclusion is provided. In case of Dual and Quad SPI modes the FIFO inclusion is mandatory.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: Multiples16
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing the SPI clock in Standard SPI mode. Please refer PG for more reference.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: Async_Clk
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This parameter should be set while choosing the core to be used in Standalone mode and if clocks to core are different.
